# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### Fixed
- **format_filter validation error**: Removed `format_filter` parameter from MCP `search_books` tool signature to eliminate "format_filter cannot be None" validation errors. The parameter was causing MCP tool schema conflicts when omitted by callers.

### Changed
- **Metadata display format**: Updated `get_book_metadata` MCP tool to properly handle Calibre API field names:
  - Changed `author` to `authors` (list format)
  - Changed `format` to `formats` (list format)
  - Added proper datetime parsing for `pubdate` field (displays as "Jan 2026" instead of ISO strings)
  - Added `pages` field display support
  - Added `comments`/notes content display
  - Added `languages` field display
  - Improved `identifiers` formatting with ISBN detection

## [0.0.2] - 03/30/2026

### Fixed
- Critical bug: Library ID was hardcoded to "books", preventing downloads from servers with different library names
  - Now automatically fetches library ID from server's `/opds` endpoint on first connection
  - CLI `--library` default changed from `"books"` to `None` (auto-detect)
  - MCP server now passes `library=None` to enable auto-detection

### Added
- File-based logging for MCP server (`~/.bookworm/mcp_server.log`)
- File-based logging for download operations (`~/.bookworm/download.log`)
  - Logs include: function calls, parameters, book metadata (title, author, formats), download progress, errors with stack traces
- Debug-level logging for HTTP request/response details when enabled

## [0.0.1] - 03/29/2026

### Added
- Initial release
- CLI interface for searching Calibre content servers
- Download functionality for ebooks
- Configuration management for server URLs